last_episode_to_air.name: Live Finale
last_episode_to_air.overview: In her opening monologue, host Chelsea Handler talks about what she did today at the studio on this the last day of the show, including the last communal shower she had in the Chelsea Lately shower facility. Chelsea and Chuy bring on her current stable of round table regulars. What Chelsea believes is going to be three of her closest celebrity friends, Mary McCormack - her best friend - Jennifer Aniston, and Sandra Bullock, providing a gracious send-off ends up being what they hope will be more useful for Chelsea's life. Chelsea's ex-lover 50 Cent and G-Unit perform their new single, "Watch Me". Chuy, via a prepared video, talks about what this show and Chelsea have meant to him. Miley Cyrus, in tribute to it being the last show, performs the pop classic, "It's Over". And many of Chelsea's musical friends, and some non-musical friends, help her serenade E!, to who she is grateful for the past seven years.

episodes.name: Sam Morgante
episodes.overview: Chelsea Handler talks about the things she has in common with Miley Cyrus. Chelsea and her round table panelists John Caparulo, Sarah Tiana and Ross Mathews discuss Cyrus smoking a joint on stage at the MTV EMA's, Tom Cruise's deposition that his job is as grueling as fighting the war in Afghanistan, and California legislators discussing a law that would require porn actors to wear goggles to protect their eyes from exposure to bodily fluids. And Chelsea's guest, former White House chef Sam Morgante, prepares some of the Commander in Chiefs' favorite dishes.

episodes.name: Avril Lavigne
episodes.overview: Chelsea Handler talks about her thoughts on the recent Miss Universe Pageant. Chelsea and her round table panelists April Richardson, Josh Wolf and Loni Love discuss Chelsea being in trouble with the Catholic League for a joke she made about having an abortion, Sarah Palin's latest book about what she perceives to be the war on Christmas, the upcoming Single's Day in China, a cat caught smuggling marijuana into a prison in Moldova, and why Chelsea's dog is currently wearing a collar. And Chelsea chats with guest Avril Lavigne.

episodes.name: Tim Allen

episodes.name: Live Finale
episodes.overview: In her opening monologue, host Chelsea Handler talks about what she did today at the studio on this the last day of the show, including the last communal shower she had in the Chelsea Lately shower facility. Chelsea and Chuy bring on her current stable of round table regulars. What Chelsea believes is going to be three of her closest celebrity friends, Mary McCormack - her best friend - Jennifer Aniston, and Sandra Bullock, providing a gracious send-off ends up being what they hope will be more useful for Chelsea's life. Chelsea's ex-lover 50 Cent and G-Unit perform their new single, "Watch Me". Chuy, via a prepared video, talks about what this show and Chelsea have meant to him. Miley Cyrus, in tribute to it being the last show, performs the pop classic, "It's Over". And many of Chelsea's musical friends, and some non-musical friends, help her serenade E!, to who she is grateful for the past seven years.
